        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I got an issue during the validation on an array.\nFor an element with : \n$_allowEmpty = true;\n$_isArray = true;\n$_required = false;\n\nInto Zend_Form_Element::isValid($value, $context = null) :\n    If you submit an empty value, you'll have $value = Array([0] => )\n    so this code can't work :\n        if (('' === $value) && !$this->isRequired() && $this->getAllowEmpty()) {\n            return true;\n        }\n\nSo I changed this code :\n    foreach ($value as $val) {\n        if (('' === $val) && !$this->isRequired() && $this->getAllowEmpty()) {\n            continue;\n        }\n        if (!$validator->isValid($val, $context)) {\n            $result = false;\n            $messages = array_merge($messages, $validator->getMessages());\n            $errors   = array_merge($errors,   $validator->getErrors());\n        }\n    }\n\nHopping it's can help you..."
        },
